&lt;P&gt;(OOC: Danke, Herr Aerosmith.&nbsp; Am I correct in assuming your faction is the Tripredacus?)&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;The occupant of the pod did nothing in its protoform state as Quilldart recklessly fired close to the pod to unearth it.&nbsp; While Quilldart succeeded, he also managed to partially hit the pod a few times.&nbsp; But lucky for him his weaponsfire only did damage to the outside of the stasis pod and did no damage to any vital systems.&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P&gt;Quilldart put foreign chip into the pod&#39;s systems.&nbsp; Its internal computer immediately identified the chip as a foreign object that was potentially hazardous to the protoform within, and did its best to fight the chip, but in vain as the Maximal within the pod was corrupted to serve Galvatron.&nbsp; With the pod finally above ground the scanning compartment could reach into the sky and initate the scanning process, but it was interrupted as the pod already had a preset form for this Maximal, now Galvatron&#39;s servant.&nbsp; Even the Galvapred chip couldn&#39;t override this.&nbsp; So the scanning equipment went back inside as the protoform was changed.&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P&gt;With a slight hiss the pod opened, and a fourteen foot former Maximal of black, red, and gold coloring hopped out, a head holding his head as if hurt.&nbsp; His optics searched about him as he saw a battle raging at the Tripredacus base.&nbsp; Confused, he turned and saw Quilldart and gave him a puzzled look.&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P&gt;&quot;Wh...what&#39;s going on?&quot; was all Teufel could ask as his insides screamed out something was wrong, but were silenced by the Galvapred chip within Teufel&#39;s metallic head.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;
